1️⃣ sniff()

Captures network packets from your network interface.

sniff(prn=packet_callback)

prn → Calls the function for every captured packet.

2️⃣ packet.haslayer(IP)

Checks if the packet contains an IP layer.

3️⃣ Extract Packet Information
packet[IP].src
packet[IP].dst

Gets Source IP and Destination IP.

4️⃣ Identify Protocol

The program detects:

TCP

UDP

ICMP

5️⃣ Read Payload
packet["Raw"].load

Shows the actual data being transmitted.
